<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
{{> head}}
<body>
     <header>
       	{{> nav nav}}
    </header>
	<main>
		<h1>{{title}}</h1>

		<article class="content">
			<div>
				<img class="recipe_img" src=
					{{#if image}}
						"{{image}}" alt="{{alt}}"
					{{else}}
						"assets/glitter-pot.png" alt=""
					{{/if}}
				/>
				<section class="details">
					<h2>Details</h2>
					<ul>
						<li class="content_li">Oven temperature: 180ยบ</li>
						<li class="content_li">Servings: ~30</li>
					</ul>
				</section>
			</div>
			<h2>Ingredients</h2>
			<ul>
				<li class="content_li">200 g of white flour</li>
				<li class="content_li">1 bag of baking powder</li>
				<li class="content_li">100g of non refined cane sugar</li>
				<li class="content_li">125g of melted butter (and cooled down before using)</li>
				<li class="content_li">1 egg</li>
				<li class="content_li">1 egg yolk</li>
				<li class="content_li">2 teaspoons of vanilla extract</li>
				<li class="content_li">100g of dark chocolate chips</li>
			</ul>
			<h2>Steps</h2>
			<div class="steps">
					 <p class="step">Preheat oven at 180ยบ. </p>
			<p class="step">Mix all dry ingredients in your main bowl, and set aside. </p>
			<p class="step">Mix butter, eggs and vanilla together, in a separate bowl. </p>

			<p class="step">Incorporate in the dry mix until homogenous, with a wooden spoon.
				Add as much flour as needed, until the consitency is right:
				it must be solid enough so that it can be manipulate dby hand,
				without the dough staying on your fingers. </p>
			<p class="step">Make small balls of dough by hand, and place them on a baking sheet, on an over plate.
				Keep them ~3 cm apart, to make sure they don't blend together when expanding. </p>
			<p class="step">Bake for 12-15 minutes, depending on the size of the balls</p>
			<p class="step">Don't remove from the sheet until cooled down, to avoid breaking them. </p>
			</div>

		</article>
	</main>

    {{> footer footer}}
</body>
</html>